<p>Suppose I have the following models:</p>  <pre><code>class Product(models.Model):     tags = models.CharField(max_length=50)     created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)     type = models.ForeignKey(ContentType, related_name='type')  class Flash(models.Model):     name = models.CharField(max_length=50)  class Lense(models.Model):     name = models.CharField(max_length=50) </code></pre>  <p>Is it possible in django admin, instead of having <code>pk</code> to the type field on the Product form, to have all the forms that model with that <code>pk</code> has?</p>